                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/418.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargè <persName type="from">Brown</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">La Union, Salvador,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reports that, on account of health, the President of Nicaragua will be unable to
                    attend the conference, and both countries will be represented <pb facs="0781"
                        n="631" xml:id="pg_631"/> by ministers for foreign affairs. The conference
                    should open day after to-morrow. Also reports that advices from Tegucigalpa
                    indicate a disquieting situation because of absence of the recognized
                    responsible Government.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
